cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you reference this tool, please cite it as below."
title: "ExposureCheck: self-audit your social-media export for re-identification (mosaic) risk"
abstract: >-
  A local-first, no-dossier command-line tool that runs adversarial LLM
  inference over your own Reddit and X/Twitter exports to surface, by category,
  what a mosaic re-identification attack could reconstruct — so you can generalise
  or edit the highest-risk posts. Bring-your-own-model (cloud or local).
type: software
authors:
  - name: "Cora Aegis"
    website: "https://cypherpunkguide.com"
version: "0.1.0"
keywords:
  - privacy
  - opsec
  - deanonymization
  - re-identification
  - osint-defense
  - mosaic
url: "https://cypherpunkguide.com"
